  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u2019\u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb8\u0bcd\u2019",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel 'pass' introduced",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power and Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekara has said that the 'National Fuel Permit' (PASS) will be introduced to ensure weekly fuel allocation for motorists.",
        "The Minister mentioned that the 'National Fuel Pass' will ensure weekly fuel allocation for which a vehicle will be registered under a National Identity Card number and a QR code will be allotted once the vehicle's chassis number and other details are verified.",
        "He informed that fuel will be dispensed for 2 days of the week according to the last digit of vehicle number plate using QR code.",
        "The Minister also mentioned that further details will be released today at 12.30 noon."
      ],
